Walk through `workspaces.ts` to see all store concepts working together.

**Step 1:** Two writable stores hold the raw data
```typescript
export const workspaces = writable<Workspace[]>([]);
export const activeWorkspace = writable<WorkspaceDetail | null>(null);
```
*File: `frontend/src/lib/stores/workspaces.ts:5-6`*

**Step 2:** A derived store extracts a convenient computed value
```typescript
export const activeWorkspaceId = derived(activeWorkspace, ($ws) => $ws?.id ?? null);
```
*File: `frontend/src/lib/stores/workspaces.ts:7`*

**Step 3:** `setActiveWorkspace` orchestrates API calls and multiple store updates
```typescript
await openWorkspace(id);
const detail = await getWorkspace(id);
activeWorkspace.set(detail);
await loadWorkspaces();
```
*File: `frontend/src/lib/stores/workspaces.ts:17-27`*

**Step 4:** `clearActiveWorkspace` is the simplest possible store operation — setting to null triggers the derived store to recompute
```typescript
export function clearActiveWorkspace() {
	activeWorkspace.set(null);
}
```
*File: `frontend/src/lib/stores/workspaces.ts:29-31`*

**Key Insight:** A single call to `setActiveWorkspace(7)` updates three stores (`activeWorkspace`, `activeWorkspaceId`, `workspaces`) and causes every component subscribed to any of them to re-render with fresh data.

